<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Gong better than Chorus for sales coaching?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, Gong has stronger sales coaching workflows in 2026. It offers more granular rep scorecards, deal risk signals tied directly to call behavior, and a larger library of third-party coaching integrations. Chorus coaching features are solid but trail Gong's depth, particularly for large sales teams."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does Gong cost per seat in 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Gong typically runs $130 to $160 per seat per month in production deployments. List pricing is rarely what you pay. At 20+ seats with an annual contract, negotiated rates often land closer to $110 to $130. Always negotiate; Gong sales reps have significant discount authority."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between Gong and Chorus?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Both platforms record, transcribe, and analyze sales calls. The key differences: Gong leads in deal intelligence depth and coaching ecosystem. Chorus offers a ZoomInfo data bundle for customers already on that platform. Pricing is comparable, but Chorus can be more flexible at lower seat counts. For most teams without a ZoomInfo relationship, Gong is the stronger choice."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Should I use Chorus if I already have ZoomInfo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, if you are already a ZoomInfo customer, bundling Chorus into your ZoomInfo contract is worth evaluating seriously. The combined pricing can be meaningfully cheaper than buying Gong separately, and the integration between ZoomInfo data and Chorus call intelligence adds real signal for prospecting and ICP refinement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use Gong or Chorus with HubSpot?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, both Gong and Chorus integrate with HubSpot. Gong's HubSpot integration is more mature, with bidirectional deal field sync and activity logging. Chorus also supports HubSpot but has historically been more tightly coupled with Salesforce. Either works for a HubSpot shop; verify the specific fields you need in a trial before committing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a cheaper alternative to Gong for a small sales team?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For teams with fewer than 10 AEs, Fathom is the most commonly recommended alternative. It offers free call recording and transcription with AI summaries, and paid tiers are a fraction of Gong or Chorus pricing. Pairing Fathom with Claude for deeper analysis gives most small teams everything Gong provides at under $30 per seat per month."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Gong or Chorus record Zoom calls automatically?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, both Gong and Chorus can record Zoom calls automatically using a bot that joins scheduled meetings. Setup requires connecting your calendar and Zoom account. Gong's bot is widely considered more reliable and less obtrusive. Both also support Google Meet and Microsoft Teams recording."}]}]}</script>
